vulnerability_tickets_check.py is used to create/update jira tickets.

The following Jenkins jobs are setup to run this script:

* https://server.jenkins.couchbase.com/view/blackduck/job/update_jira_from_vulnerability_scan
  This job is kicked off after blackduck-detect-scan.  It compares vulnerabilities of BOMs
  against existing tickets in Jira's VULN project; create/update/close tickets accordingly

* https://server.jenkins.couchbase.com/view/blackduck/job/Update_jira_from_blackduck_hub
  This job runs daily.  It goes through all the projects and versions; looks for journal
  entries of new vulnerabilities and update corresponding Jira tickets.

Usage:
    python3 vulnerability_tickets_check.py scan -p ${PRODUCT} -v ${VERSION}
    i.e.
    python3 vulnerability_tickets_check.py -p couchbase-server -v 7.6.4

    python3 vulnerability_tickets_check.py knownledgebase -d ${start_date}
    i.e. python3 vulnerability_tickets_check.py knownledgebase -d 2024-10-10
         This goes through journal entries starting from 2024-10-10 until today 
